===Etymology===
From Greek [[Ἰνδία]], via Latin '''India''', derived from Ἰνδός, the '''[[Indus]]''' River. Ἰνδός itself comes from the {{Pers.}} {{FAchar|[[هند]]}} '''(Hend)''' (in [[Sanskrit]] '''[[sindhu]]''', ''river''). English in the 9th century (in King Alfred's translation of ''Orosius''), and again since the 17th century.

